  "campus_description": "ATL@ATLANTA",
  "course_description": "Accounting is called \"the language of business\" because its purpose is to measure, analyze, and report the economic effects of business transactions. In this course we will learn the rules and regulations of accounting so that you can be an informed reader of financial reports. Specifically, you will learn how to read and analyze Balance Sheets, Income Statements, and Statements of Cash Flows. We will prepare these statements as well as read real company reports. The framework learned in this course will allow you to better understand what a business does and how well it does what it does. You will become a sophisticated consumer of publicly disclosed accounting information and enhance your ability to communicate in the business world.",
